/*
 * HapticCandlestick.cpp
 * =====================
 * Drop this single file into an existing CHAI3D example project
 * (e.g. copy the "01-mydevice" example folder, replace its .cpp).
 *
 * What it does:
 *   - Opens the Novint Falcon via CHAI3D
 *   - Polls position at ~1 kHz on a dedicated high-priority thread
 *   - Aggregates samples into OHLC "packets" (candlestick bars)
 *   - Renders them with OpenGL:
 *       X axis = timestamp (rolling window)
 *       Y axis = position magnitude  sqrt(x^2 + y^2 + z^2)
 *       Bar height = magnitude delta (open vs close of each window)
 *       Wick       = high / low of each window
 *       Green bar  = magnitude increased over the window
 *       Red bar    = magnitude decreased over the window
 *
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  ADDITIONAL DEPENDENCY  (only ONE extra lib needed)
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  The CHAI3D built project already links:
 *    opengl32.lib  glu32.lib  glfw3.lib  winmm.lib  setupapi.lib  hid.lib
 *
 *  You only need to add:
 *    ws2_32.lib   <-- Winsock2 for the UDP network broadcast
 *
 *  In Visual Studio:
 *    Project → Properties → Linker → Input → Additional Dependencies
 *    Add:  ws2_32.lib
 *
 *  That is the ONLY change needed to a standard CHAI3D built project.
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 *
 * CONTROLS:
 *   ESC        quit
 *   + / -      increase / decrease candle window duration
 *   R          reset Y-axis zoom
 *   N          toggle UDP network broadcast on/off
 */

